Rarely do I find a place in which the food is inedible. However, it is at Eddy's.  I ordered a chicken salad sub with nothing on it.  How can you mess that up?  Well you can if your chicken saled contains ONLY the following ingredients: chicken, grissle, mayo.  And not even good mayo!  Hey Eddy, how about you trim the nasty white fatty stuff off your chicken before you cut it up?  No one wants to bite into that!  And how about some flavor?  Maybe some celery, or dill, or even some plain pepper.  Take a look at chicken salad ANYWHERE else and you will find more than just those boring ingredients.  I made it through a little less than half the sandwich before I gave up fighting the grissle.  The restaurant businesss is not the place to have a "do as little as you have to" attitude.  I will NOT be back!
